subject: King Kong updated, swaps .Thaw and .Why
msgSnippet: I ve updated King Kong by swapping .Thaw and .Why ù this means that the left ring finger is now for w sounds, and the left middle finger is for th sounds.
messageBody:
I've updated King Kong by swapping .Thaw and .Why — this means that the left ring finger is now for "w" sounds, and the left middle finger is for "th" sounds. If you'd like to see what it looks like, head to the underdecorated-yet-marginally-self-contained http://www.frogorbits.com/qs/virtual-keyboard/ and click in a text box. If you'd like to use it someplace, drop by quikscript.org!

I've also updated the README — hopefully it provides a clearer introduction to enabling alternate keyboard layouts in both OS X and Windows. If it still doesn't make sense, shoot me an e-mail or post to the list; I'd like to get as many people on PUA layouts as possible.

Nathan
